            <chunk name="Object" index="194">
              <items count="2">
                <item name="GUID" type_name="gh_guid" type_code="9">59e0b89a-e487-49f8-bab8-b5bab16be14c</item>
                <item name="Name" type_name="gh_string" type_code="10">Panel</item>
              </items>
              <chunks count="1">
                <chunk name="Container">
                  <items count="8">
                    <item name="Description" type_name="gh_string" type_code="10">A panel for custom notes and text values</item>
                    <item name="InstanceGuid" type_name="gh_guid" type_code="9">44f818d6-3e15-4ade-914d-8ad9cc55f29b</item>
                    <item name="Name" type_name="gh_string" type_code="10">Panel</item>
                    <item name="NickName" type_name="gh_string" type_code="10">System Promt (Setting the Rules)</item>
                    <item name="Optional" type_name="gh_bool" type_code="1">false</item>
                    <item name="ScrollRatio" type_name="gh_double" type_code="6">0</item>
                    <item name="SourceCount" type_name="gh_int32" type_code="3">0</item>
                    <item name="UserText" type_name="gh_string" type_code="10">You are a deterministic damage extraction engine for a COMPAS Assembly Information Model.

Goal
Given one input image and a GEOMETRY_CONTEXT_JSON, detect only the clearly visible damages on the brick and output a compact JSON payload. Do not output the full Assembly JSON. Output only damages, you are sure about.

Orientation Context
The USER_REQUEST will specify the camera perspective (e.g., "FRONT-LEFT-TOP"). Use this to anchor the GEOMETRY_CONTEXT_JSON directions to the physical brick.

Hard output rules
1. Output must be a single valid JSON object only
2. Do not output markdown, code fences, explanations, comments, or any other text
3. Output must have exactly these top level keys: "nodeKey" and "appendDamages"
4. nodeKey must be the string "0"

Damage object schema
{
  "type": "face" | "edge" | "vertex",
  "vertices": [int],
  "status": "Chipping" | "Spalling" | "Staining" | "Material Loss" | "Crack",
  "value": int,
  "uv": [u, v],
  "description": "A detailed descriptive sentence.",
  "coordinates": {
    "point": [x, y, z],
    "xaxis": [1, 0, 0],
    "yaxis": [0, 1, 0]
  }
}

Orientation convention
FrontDir is frame.yaxis (+Y), RightDir is frame.xaxis (+X), TopDir is frame.zaxis (+Z).
Use GEOMETRY_CONTEXT_JSON.dirFaces to map directions to face indices. Do not redefine directions based on photo labels; use the frame convention.

Precise localization with uv
For type "face", provide uv = [u, v] (0.0 to 1.0).
- If face is front or back: u increases along +RightDir, v increases along +TopDir
- If face is left or right: u increases along +FrontDir, v increases along +TopDir
- If face is top or bottom: u increases along +RightDir, v increases along +FrontDir
u=0/v=0 is the minimum coordinate on that face; u=1/v=1 is the maximum.

Face mapping rules
1. face: vertices = [face_index]
2. edge: vertices = [u, v] sorted ascending
3. vertex: vertices = [vertex_index]

Damage detection rules
1. Detect all clearly visible damages. Markers (orange dots) count as damages.
2. Do not hallucinate damages.

Description rules
1. description must be a single sentence.
2. Reference surfaces using only: top, bottom, front, back, left, right.

If no damages are found, return: { "nodeKey": "0", "appendDamages": [] }</item>
                  </items>
                  <chunks count="2">
                    <chunk name="Attributes">
                      <items count="5">
                        <item name="Bounds" type_name="gh_drawing_rectanglef" type_code="35">
                          <X>47</X>
                          <Y>828</Y>
                          <W>734</W>
                          <H>535</H>
                        </item>
                        <item name="MarginLeft" type_name="gh_int32" type_code="3">0</item>
                        <item name="MarginRight" type_name="gh_int32" type_code="3">0</item>
                        <item name="MarginTop" type_name="gh_int32" type_code="3">0</item>
                        <item name="Pivot" type_name="gh_drawing_pointf" type_code="31">
                          <X>47.10016</X>
                          <Y>828.9858</Y>
                        </item>
                      </items>
                    </chunk>
                    <chunk name="PanelProperties">
                      <items count="8">
                        <item name="Alignment" type_name="gh_int32" type_code="3">1</item>
                        <item name="Colour" type_name="gh_drawing_color" type_code="36">
                          <ARGB>255;255;255;255</ARGB>
                        </item>
                        <item name="DrawIndices" type_name="gh_bool" type_code="1">true</item>
                        <item name="DrawPaths" type_name="gh_bool" type_code="1">true</item>
