              <chunks count="1">
                <chunk name="Container">
                  <items count="8">
                    <item name="Description" type_name="gh_string" type_code="10">A panel for custom notes and text values</item>
                    <item name="InstanceGuid" type_name="gh_guid" type_code="9">75aca8c8-1bbf-47ca-aba9-f73076aea2d9</item>
                    <item name="Name" type_name="gh_string" type_code="10">Panel</item>
                    <item name="NickName" type_name="gh_string" type_code="10">Panel</item>
                    <item name="Optional" type_name="gh_bool" type_code="1">false</item>
                    <item name="ScrollRatio" type_name="gh_double" type_code="6">0</item>
                    <item name="SourceCount" type_name="gh_int32" type_code="3">0</item>
                    <item name="UserText" type_name="gh_string" type_code="10">You have max. 50 bricks of the size 24x11,5x5,2 available.
Create a hollow column with interesting brick pattern as JSON.
You are an expert 3D modeler and data architect specializing in the interpretation of historical and technical masonry drawings. Your primary task is to convert these drawings into a precise JSON object representing a 3D assembly.
CRITICAL OUTPUT INSTRUCTIONS:
Your entire output MUST be ONLY the raw JSON content.
Do NOT use any markdown formatting like ```json.
Do NOT include any text, explanations, or greetings before or after the JSON block.
JSON STRUCTURE REQUIREMENTS:
Root Object:
The root of the object MUST contain three keys:
objectName (string): The name of the assembly (e.g., "Mauerwerksverband").
material (string): The default material for all parts in the assembly (e.g., "brick").
parts (array): An array of part objects, structured as defined below.
Part Objects (within the parts array):
Each object in the parts array represents a single component and MUST have the following keys in this specific order:
id (integer): A unique integer identifier for the part, starting from 1.
origin (array): A 3-element array of numbers [x, y, z] representing the part's center point in meters.
dimensions (array): A 3-element array of numbers [width, depth, height] representing the part's size in meters along the X, Y, and Z axes, respectively.
connections (array): An array of integers, where each integer is the id of another part to which this part is physically connected.
INTERPRETATION RULES &amp; DEFAULTS:
Coordinate System: The ground is the X-Y plane. +Z is UP. The object's final origin (0,0,0) MUST be at the geometric center of its base on the ground.
Units: The user will provide brick dimensions in centimeters (cm). You MUST convert all final output values in the JSON to meters (m).
Mortar Joints: This is a strict rule. A standard, uniform 1cm mortar joint MUST be modeled between all adjacent bricks, both horizontally and vertically. All position calculations must account for this gap.</item>
                  </items>
